  "finding": "Server/proxy send and relay work is measurably slower on ylong request timing in the failing nested HTTPS-origin cells, but the extra server-side work is roughly tens to low hundreds of microseconds per request, while ylong response_read is about 1.26-1.31 ms/request. This refutes Python proxy/origin sendall/relay as a sufficient root cause and keeps the remaining target in client/runtime response-read wait behavior.",
